        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2006-11-03T11:39:05.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>The MVC implementation in 0.2.0's incubator (and current SVN) introduced pre/postDispatch() methods that are executed for every action. The stubs in the Zend_Controller_Action class do nothing by default, but you may have them do anything you desire when extending the class. Performing a _forward() action in the preDispatch() method will skip execution of the current action.</p>

